  "description": "An open-source color system of ~30 hand-tuned 12-step scales designed for building accessible UIs, from the Radix UI team. It is the industry reference for semantic step-based scales: every step has a documented use case.",
  "philosophy": "Each scale has 12 steps, each designed for at least one specific use case: 1-2 app/subtle backgrounds, 3-5 component backgrounds (normal/hover/active), 6-8 borders (subtle/interactive/strong+focus), 9-10 solid backgrounds (step 9 is the purest, highest-chroma step), 11-12 text (low/high contrast). Steps 11 and 12 are guaranteed Lc 60 and Lc 90 APCA contrast on a step-2 background of the same scale. Dark mode is not derived: every scale has a dedicated hand-tuned dark counterpart, and alpha plus wide-gamut display-p3 variants exist for every scale.",
