  "solidForeground": "white for most scales (Blue, Red, Green, Gray); Amber step 9-10 solids are designed for dark foreground text (per docs, Sky/Mint/Lime/Yellow/Amber are the bright exceptions)",
  "notes": "Values are the sRGB hex fallbacks from @radix-ui/colors@3.0.0. Each scale also ships alpha variants (grayA, blueDarkA, ...) and wide-gamut display-p3 variants (including P3 alpha) behind @supports/@media guards; those are not included here. Dark values come from the dedicated hand-tuned *-dark scales, not from inverting the light scale. Step 9 is identical in light and dark for blue (#0090ff), red (#e5484d), green (#30a46c) and amber (#ffc53d) - the solid brand color is stable across modes."
